Uh, windows has been using thumbs.bd since
Mellenium edition. It might be present in Win98SE, I don't remember that far back.
But from what I've experianced,
It's a database of the thumbnails of the photos in a folder when in VIEW as ->Thunbnails.
If you don't set the view as thumbnails, it
usually doesn't create a .db file.
